menu "Reflex OS"
    choice REFLEX_RADIO_BACKEND
        prompt "Radio backend"
        default REFLEX_RADIO_ESPNOW
        help
            Select the radio backend for the GOOSE atmospheric mesh.
            ESP-NOW requires the Wi-Fi binary blob.
            802.15.4 is blob-free but uses a different radio.

        config REFLEX_RADIO_ESPNOW
            bool "ESP-NOW (Wi-Fi)"

        config REFLEX_RADIO_802154
            bool "IEEE 802.15.4 (blob-free)"
    endchoice
    config REFLEX_KERNEL_SCHEDULER
        bool "Enable Reflex kernel supervisor and port assembly"
        default n
        help
            Activates the Reflex kernel layer on top of FreeRTOS:
            - Wraps rtos_int_enter/exit with our port assembly
            - Creates the kernel supervisor task (purpose-modulated
              scheduling, Hebbian priority, holon lifecycle)
            - Registers a 1kHz tick ISR on SYSTIMER TARGET1
            FreeRTOS remains as the scheduling HAL. A complete
            standalone task backend exists in kernel/reflex_task_kernel.c.
endmenu
